The paper discusses the impact of social influence on security decision-making, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves an online controlled experiment with human participants, which relates to social influence (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential exploitation of social media for compromising security, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social computing (cs.SOC).
